HEADWORD: Hastings sands
<hw>Has"tings sands`</hw> <pr>(s⟦acr⟧ndz`)</pr>. <fld>(Geol.)</fld>
<def>The lower group of the Wealden formation; -- so called from its
development around <etsep>Hastings</etsep>, in Sussex,
England.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

